	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_IWAN_PALACE">
			<Text>[ICON_GOLD] Iwan Palace</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_IWAN_PALACE_HELP">
			<Text>+4 [ICON_GOLD] Gold from every [ICON_RES_GOLD] Gold and [ICON_RES_SILVER] Silver resource worked by this City. Improves global [ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Happiness. Only Persia may build it.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_IWAN_PALACE_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Persian unique replacement for the Mint, the Iwan Palace retains the normal gold bonus from resources, but can be built in any City. It also increases global [ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Happiness, so you'll get the full bonus regardless of City [ICON_CITIZEN] Population. Build them early to help generate points toward [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Ages.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_IWAN_PALACE_TEXT">
			<Text>
				An iwan is a rectangular hall or space, usually vaulted, walled on three sides, with one end entirely open. The formal gateway to the iwan is called pishtaq, a Persian term for a portal projecting from the facade of a building, usually decorated with calligraphy bands, glazed tilework, and geometric designs. The Persians favored the iwan form, and adopted it into much of their architecture.
			</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>

